main event: A witness reported observing an unusual aerial object in Cincinnati, Ohio, on September 7, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as a black, formless mass approximately 30-40 feet long and 10-15 feet wide., The sighting lasted for approximately 2-3 minutes before the object disappeared from view., The object was observed moving erratically and at high speed., No sound was heard during the sighting and no other witnesses were reported., The report concluded that insufficient data was available for a definitive identification.
sighted object: a black, formless mass in the sky
witness description: private citizen who observed the sighting
